In Windows, search: Environment Variables
• It's in system properties
--> Advanced
--> Environment Variables
• In the new window, at the bottom, find 'Path', select it, and click 'Edit'
Here you will add Python to the Windows path


Open cmd, type: python
• It will tell you which version you have installed
• WHen you see the 3 arrows below, it means whatever you write next will be in python (ex. print("hello"))
